						<div class="postbody">But then the PS1, PS2, and GameCube have nicer DMA controllers, so that they can keep the game (either menu animations or a different part of the map) running while another part of the game loads into RAM. The FDS is all cycle-timed PIO, meaning that the CPU has to wait for each bit to come in.</div>

